---
name: js-cps-intrinsic-rewrite
backends: [int, js]
---

# a `RuntimeCall` intrinsic inside a CPS (effectful) body is still rewritten

Regression for the JS backend (busi deep-offline standalone bundle). A call to a
`RuntimeCall` intrinsic (here `nowMillis` → `Date.now`) that lands in a CPS
context — because the enclosing function is effectful (`stamped` performs
`Box.read`) — fell through `genCpsApply`'s "regular call" path, which emitted the
bare source name (`nowMillis()`). `genExpr`/`dispatchIntrinsicJs` only rewrote
`Term.Apply` sites, so the CPS path missed it and the bare name was undefined in
a standalone `emit-js` bundle. `genCpsApply` now applies the same rewrite.

[runBox, Box](./lib/effect-box.ssc)

```scalascript
def stamped(): Boolean =
  Box.read(1)        // forces `stamped` effectful → its body is CPS-lowered
  nowMillis() > 0    // a RuntimeCall intrinsic reached via the CPS path

println(runBox(() => stamped()))
```
